The symbol shall not touch or overlap other brown symbols. Location is the centre of gravity of the symbol, and the symbol is orientated to north.
Footprint: 12 m x 6 m.</description><point_symbol inner_radius="1500" inner_color="-1" outer_width="0" outer_color="-1" elements="1"><element><symbol type="2" code=""><line_symbol color="8" line_width="270" minimum_length="0" join_style="1" cap_style="0" start_offset="0" end_offset="0" segment_length="5166" end_length="0" show_at_least_one_symbol="true" minimum_mid_symbol_count="0" minimum_mid_symbol_count_when_closed="0" dash_length="5166" break_length="1292" dashes_in_group="1" in_group_break_length="647" mid_symbols_per_spot="1" mid_symbol_distance="0"/></symbol><object type="1"><coords count="7">465 -304 1;465 -48;257 161;0 161 1;-256 161;-465 -48;-465 -304;</coords><pattern rotation="0"><coord x="0" y="0"/></pattern></object></element></point_symbol></symbol>
<symbol type="1" id="17" code="112" name="Pit"><description>Pits and holes with distinct steep sides which cannot be shown to scale using symbol Earth bank (104).
Minimum depth: 1 m, minimum width: 1 m.
A pit larger than 5 m x 5 m should normally be exaggerated and drawn using Earth bank (104). Pits without steep sides are represented with symbol Small depression (111).
The symbol shall not touch or overlap other brown symbols. Location is the centre of gravity of the symbol, and the symbol is orientated to north.
Footprint: 10.5 m x 12 m.</description><point_symbol inner_radius="1350" inner_color="-1" outer_width="0" outer_color="-1" elements="1"><element><symbol type="4" code=""><area_symbol inner_color="8" min_area="0" patterns="0"/></symbol><object type="1"><coords count="7">231 -453;525 -453;0 734;-525 -453;-231 -453;0 75;231 -453 2;</coords><pattern rotation="0"><coord x="0" y="0"/></pattern></object></element></point_symbol></symbol>
<symbol type="4" id="18" code="113" name="Broken ground"><description>An area of pits and / or knolls which is too intricate to be shown in detail, or other types of rough and uneven ground that is clearly distinguishable but has little impact on runnability.
The dots should be randomly distributed but not interfere with the representation of important terrain features and objects.
The minimum number of dots is three (footprint 10 m x 10 m).
The maximum centre to centre distance between neighbouring dots is 0.6 mm.
The minimum centre to centre distance between neighbouring dots is 0.5 mm.
Contours should not be cut in broken ground areas.
The dots shall not be arranged to form a single point wide line.</description><area_symbol inner_color="-1" min_area="0" rotatable="true" patterns="1"><pattern type="2" angle="0" no_clipping="2" rotatable="true" line_spacing="1500" line_offset="0" offset_along_line="0" point_distance="1500"><symbol type="1" code="" name="Pattern fill 1"><point_symbol rotatable="true" inner_radius="1500" inner_color="-1" outer_width="0" outer_color="-1" elements="4"><element><symbol type="1" code=""><point_symbol inner_radius="150" inner_color="8" outer_width="0" outer_color="-1" elements="0"/></symbol><object type="0"><coords count="1">-255 -810;</coords></object></element><element><symbol type="1" code=""><point_symbol inner_radius="150" inner_color="8" outer_width="0" outer_color="-1" elements="0"/></symbol><object type="0"><coords count="1">-1125 -930;</coords></object></element><element><symbol type="1" code=""><point_symbol inner_radius="150" inner_color="8" outer_width="0" outer_color="-1" elements="0"/></symbol><object type="0"><coords count="1">-210 -1545;</coords></object></element><element><symbol type="1" code=""><point_symbol inner_radius="150" inner_color="8" outer_width="0" outer_color="-1" elements="0"/></symbol><object type="0"><coords count="1">-870 -1725;</coords></object></element></point_symbol></symbol></pattern></area_symbol></symbol>
<symbol type="1" id="19" code="113.1" name="Broken ground, individual dot"><description>An area of pits and / or knolls which is too intricate to be shown in detail, or other types of rough and uneven ground that is clearly distinguishable but has little impact on runnability.
The dots should be randomly distributed but not interfere with the representation of important terrain features and objects.
The minimum number of dots is three (footprint 10 m x 10 m).
The maximum centre to centre distance between neighbouring dots is 0.6 mm.
The minimum centre to centre distance between neighbouring dots is 0.5 mm.
Contours should not be cut in broken ground areas.
The dots shall not be arranged to form a single point wide line.
Density: 3-4 dots / mm².</description><point_symbol inner_radius="150" inner_color="8" outer_width="0" outer_color="-1" elements="0"/></symbol>
<symbol type="4" id="20" code="114" name="Very broken ground"><description>An area of pits and/or knolls, which is too intricate to be shown in detail, or other types of rough and uneven ground that is clearly distinguishable and affects runnability.
The dots should be randomly distributed but not interfere with the representation of important terrain features and objects.
